Note: Sample 6 â€” String manipulation and advanced text operations.

Note: Basic string operations.
Let sentence be "the quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog".
Let wordLen be the length of sentence.
Say the sentence has, wordLen, characters.
Let loud be uppercase of sentence.
Say in uppercase, loud.
Let quiet be lowercase of loud.
Say in lowercase, quiet.

Note: Trim whitespace.
Let padded be    hello world    .
Let clean be trim padded.
Say cleaned text is, clean.

Note: Replace text.
Let msg be I love dogs very much.
Let newMsg be replace dogs in msg with cats.
Say after replace, newMsg.

Note: Split a sentence into words.
Let csv be apple banana cherry date elderberry.
Let fruits be split csv by banana.
Let fruitCount be the length of fruits.
Say we have, fruitCount, fruits.
For each fruit in fruits do the following.
  Say fruit.
End for.

Note: Join a list back into a string.
Let sep be and.
Let joined be join fruits with sep.
Say joined list, joined.

Note: String contains check.
Let myText be hello wonderful world.
Let hasWord be myText contains wonderful.
If hasWord equals true then do the following.
  Say the text contains wonderful.
Otherwise do the following.
  Say wonderful was not found.
End if.
Let hasBye be myText contains goodbye.
If hasBye equals false then do the following.
  Say goodbye was not found.
End if.

Note: Index of in a string.
Let pos be index of world in myText.
Say world starts at position, pos.

Note: Repeat a string.
Let star be x.
Let divider be repeat star 20 times.
Say divider.

Note: Type conversion.
Let numText be 42.
Let asNum be as a number numText.
Let doubled be asNum * 2.
Say doubled is, doubled.
Let numVal be 3.14.
Let asStr be as text numVal.
Say numeric value, asStr.
